Key Match Events: England lost half their batting lineup now.
Malan top edges a pull and is caught.
Dropped catch off the first ball of the 11th, now another off the second
Adair was in play at long off but he misjudges attempted lofted shot, it ends up bouncing off his outstretched hands.
Post-Match Reflections: What a massive win this is. Not only does this seal a first-ever T20 World Cup Super 12 win for them, this also throws the group wide open.
This win is no accident, Ireland have been absolutely brilliant throughout this match.
Balbirnie, Adair and McCarthy have gone over to the tiny but significant Irish crowd where they are showered with hugs and kisses.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was called off after a rain delay in the 15th over
The result now throws Group 1 wide open with five of the six teams now on two points
Ireland have recorded a famous win, their first in the Super 12 stage of a T20 World Cup
